data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc` with native-sized integers.** Both `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>` work:

```csharp
Span<nint>  signed   = stackalloc nint[5];
Span<nuint> unsigned = stackalloc nuint[5];
```

On this 64-bit system, `nint`/`nuint` are 8 bytes each. This feature has been available since C# 9 (when `nint`/`nuint` were introduced) combined with the `stackalloc`-to-`Span<T>` support from C# 7.2+.
